&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At GFiber, we believe that great internet has the power to drive innovation, strengthen communities, enable the impossible, and do all the everyday things that make all of our world go round. And the job of creating better internet is never done - so we’re growing! Our team is committed to building a place where people who want to make a difference can grow their careers and find their spot to belong.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;GFiber is an Alphabet company that brings Google Fiber and Google Fiber Webpass internet services to homes and businesses across the United States. Our teams are expanding as we connect more cities and people to exceptional internet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The application window will be open until at least &lt;strong&gt;July 12th, 2026&lt;/strong&gt;. This opportunity will remain online based on business needs which may be before or after the specified date.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role is not eligible for immigration sponsorship.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role you will design and develop scalable, efficient, and secure backend services using Spring Boot and JVM languages (preferably Kotlin). This role requires a strong understanding of microservice architecture, RESTful APIs, design patterns, and distributed systems, along with the ability to lead technical initiatives, mentor team members, and drive architectural decisions. As a lead, you will play a critical role in shaping the backend infrastructure, ensuring high performance, scalability, and reliability to support our growing business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the design and implementation of robust, scalable, and maintainable backend systems using microservice architecture principles. Define and enforce best practices for system design, including scalability, fault tolerance, and performance optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain high-quality backend services and RESTful APIs using Spring Boot and JVM languages (Kotlin and Java). Write clean, efficient, and testable code adhering to modern software engineering standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design systems to handle high traffic and large datasets, leveraging distributed systems concepts such as load balancing, caching (e.g., Redis, Memcached), and message queues (e.g., Kafka, RabbitMQ).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with frontend developers, DevOps engineers, product managers, and other stakeholders to deliver end-to-end solutions that meet business requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and maintain technical documentation for architecture, APIs, and processes to facilitate knowledge sharing and onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deploy and manage containerized services on Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) or Cloud Run.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement deep tracking and monitoring for non-deterministic AI agent behaviors using Google Cloud Observability (Stackdriver) or OpenTelemetry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At a minimum, we would like you to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Information technology, a similar engineering discipline, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years of software design and full stack development experience in Java and/or Kotlin.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years of experience with API development for customer-facing applications.&lt;/li&gt;
