&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At GFiber, we believe that great internet has the power to drive innovation, strengthen communities, enable the impossible, and do all the everyday things that make all of our world go round. And the job of creating better internet is never done - so we’re growing! Our team is committed to building a place where people who want to make a difference can grow their careers and find their spot to belong.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;GFiber is an Alphabet company that brings Google Fiber and Google Fiber Webpass internet services to homes and businesses across the United States. Our teams are expanding as we connect more cities and people to exceptional internet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The application window will be open until at least &lt;strong&gt;June 28th, 2026&lt;/strong&gt;. This opportunity will remain online based on business needs which may be before or after the specified date.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;This role is not eligible for immigration sponsorship.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced and technically proficient Sales Engineer to join our team. The ideal candidate will possess a strong background in the commercial telecommunications industry, with deep expertise in internet services (e.g., Dedicated Internet Access, Broadband, Wireless Internet), a comprehensive understanding of networking solutions (e.g., SD-WAN, VPN, LAN/WAN technologies) and passive optical networks and their deployment. This role is critical in providing technical pre-sales support, designing tailored solutions, and serving as a subject matter expert for our sales force and prospective clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Pre-Sales Support:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary technical resource for the sales team, accompanying sales executives on client calls, presentations, and solution demonstrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct in-depth technical discovery sessions with prospective clients to understand their business needs, current infrastructure, and technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate complex technical concepts into clear, concise, and business-oriented language for non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solution Design &amp;amp; Architecture:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and architect customized internet and networking solutions that address client challenges and align with their strategic objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop detailed technical proposals, solution diagrams, bills of material (BOMs), and statements of work (SOWs).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product development, network operations, and implementation teams to ensure proposed solutions are feasible, scalable, and supportable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proof of Concept &amp;amp; Demonstrations:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and execute technical demonstrations, proof-of-concepts (POCs), and pilot projects to showcase the capabilities and benefits of our solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Address technical questions, concerns, and objections from potential clients with confidence and expertise.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Subject Matter Expertise &amp;amp; Training:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert (SME) on our internet and networking service portfolio, staying current with industry trends, emerging technologies, and competitor offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical training and enablement to the sales team on new products, services, and best practices.&

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At GFiber, we believe that great internet has the power to drive innovation, strengthen communities, enable the impossible, and do all the everyday things that make all of our world go round. And the job of creating better internet is never done - so we’re growing! Our team is committed to building a place where people who want to make a difference can grow their careers and find their spot to belong.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;GFiber is an Alphabet company that brings Google Fiber and Google Fiber Webpass internet services to homes and businesses across the United States. Our teams are expanding as we connect more cities and people to exceptional internet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The application window will be open until at least &lt;strong&gt;June 12, 2026&lt;/strong&gt;. This opportunity will remain online based on business needs which may be before or after the specified date.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
