&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At GFiber, we believe that great internet has the power to drive innovation, strengthen communities, enable the impossible, and do all the everyday things that make all of our world go round. And the job of creating better internet is never done - so we’re growing! Our team is committed to building a place where people who want to make a difference can grow their careers and find their spot to belong.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;GFiber is an Alphabet company that brings Google Fiber and Google Fiber Webpass internet services to homes and businesses across the United States. Our teams are expanding as we connect more cities and people to exceptional internet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The application window will be open until at least &lt;strong&gt;June 1, 2026&lt;/strong&gt;. This opportunity will remain online based on business needs which may be before or after the specified date.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Field Operations team is responsible for the installation, maintenance, and repair of residential and small business services. Within the Field Operations department, the Field Service Center team is responsible for dispatching and technical support of GFiber&#39;s Field Technicians, helping to expand and maintain GFiber&#39;s Wired and Wireless customer installations and network construction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Field Services Center Technician II supports the dispatch and technical support of: installing and repair of GFiber services, repair and maintenance of Outside and Inside Plant, planned maintenance, and preventative maintenance. Your primary responsibilities will require the use of service support software such as Salesforce - Field Service Lightning (FSL), Oracle Field Service Cloud (OFSC), GIS mapping systems&amp;nbsp; and understanding of how to diagnose and correct all service impacting root causes from the central office, remote terminal or hut location to the customer premise equipments such as:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Impairments to/with all connections&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drop cabling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Network interface units, patch panels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Media cabinets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ONTs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inside wiring (fiber, ethernet , including backup powering, UPS, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Media gateways, Modems, Routers, switches&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OSP Cabling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active electronics (including CWDM and DWDM applications)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve complex issues by troubleshooting impacted residential and small business services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinates multiple repair and maintenance resources for Outside Plant (OSP) on concurrent incidents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate install fulfillment dispatch including route optimization and handling calls from technicians.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have knowledge of installation and test of Ethernet jacks, making cross connects in telecom spaces (MDF, IDF, HDF) working with fiber optic cables, installing radio mounts, tuning microwave point-to-point radios and performing installation/construction duties, maintenance and troubleshooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigate complex customer interactions with exceptional client service, professionalism, and thoroughness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be proficient with computers and will be expected to adhere to company entry policies, both time bound and in verbiage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At a minimum we&#39;d like you to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years experience in Fiber to the Home (FTTH) / Gigabit Passive Optical Network (GPON) /10 Gigabit Passive Optical Network (XGS) network construction and/or large scale fiber network deployments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;l

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;At GFiber, we believe that great internet has the power to drive innovation, strengthen communities, enable the impossible, and do all the everyday things that make all of our world go round. And the job of creating better internet is never done - so we’re growing! Our team is committed to building a place where people who want to make a difference can grow their careers and find their spot to belong.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;GFiber is an Alphabet company that brings Google Fiber and Google Fiber Webpass internet services to homes and businesses across the United States. Our teams are expanding as we connect more cities and people to exceptional internet.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The application window will be open until at least &lt;strong&gt;June 15, 2026&lt;/strong&gt; . This opportunity will remain online based on business needs which may be before or after the specified date.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Field Services Center Technician supports GFiber’s Install and Repair technicians with Wired and Wireless customer installation and service on a rotating schedule. The Install Services Scheduler position is focused on installing and servicing GFiber Services in the customer’s premise.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Field Operations team is responsible for the installation, maintenance, and repair of residential and small business services.&amp;nbsp; For the Install Services Scheduler, primary responsibilities will require an understanding of how to manage install and repair work schedules as well as optimize field service platforms for efficient operations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Install Services Scheduler will be required to work 40 plus hours per week, and must have the&amp;nbsp; ability to work non-standard working hours including nights, weekends, holidays, and differing work rotations/shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job responsibilities include, but are not limited to dispatch support of:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creation of daily schedule/routes for Installation and Repair of GFiber Services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Routing GFiber Installation resources in real time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting routes and adjusting based on defined priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining field service platforms routing logic and technician registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalation management of routes/appointments.&amp;nbsp; This includes phone and chat contact with Install and Repair technicians to assist with dispatch related issues.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to the above items in the Role Description:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executes well defined processes and procedures requiring strong attention to detail with operational excellence; and offers guidance to teammates&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Navigates complex customer interactions with exceptional client service, professionalism, and thoroughness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills, both internally with colleagues and externally during customer interactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Candidates must be proficient with computers and will be expected to adhere to company entry policies, both time bound and verbiage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At a minimum we&#39;d like you to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1 year in Telecommunications or other fulfillment related services&lt;/li&gt;
