&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GFiber is seeking a strategic, growth-oriented Wireless Product Manager to spearhead the strategy, development, and commercialization of our next-generation wireless portfolio. In this role, you will hold end-to-end product ownership of three segments: MVNO (Mobile Virtual Network Operator) cellular services, Fixed Wireless Access (FWA), and Managed Wi-Fi solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your objective is to build a unified product strategy to manage our wireless solutions.&amp;nbsp; You will blend technical acumen with strong go-to-market strategy to capture market share in a highly dynamic wireless landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you&#39;ll:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define the vision, product lifecycle, and multi-year roadmap for our combined wireless portfolio (MVNO Mobile, FWA, and Managed Wi-Fi), ensuring a cohesive wireless strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the strategic engagement and product integrations with our underlying MNNO partner to develop mobile plans, eSIM capabilities, and related operational capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the expansion of our FWA solutions, including deployment strategy for our Webpass portfolio&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the lifecycle of our Managed Wi-Fi solutions and expand to new business segments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering, Operations, and vendors to ensure flawless product delivery, seamless zero-touch provisioning, and robust support models&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;At a minimum we&#39;d like you to have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Business, Engineering, a similar field, or relevant practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10 years of Product Management experience within the Telecommunications, Managed Service Provider, or Wireless/Cellular industries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience with MVNO operational frameworks (OSS/BSS integrations, SIM/eSIM management, data billing architectures).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of 5G network capabilities, including millimeter wave (mmWave) and CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service) config.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It&#39;s preferred if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MBA or similar advanced degree.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Managed Wi-Fi solutions, including WLAN deployment architectures and IEEE standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of cellular traffic prioritization frameworks, including Quality of Service (QoS) configurations, network slicing capabilities, and data-throttling policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
